\details{
The package implements three main sampling approaches:

\itemize{
\item \strong{Simple Random Sampling} (\code{\link[=ss_random]{ss_random()}}): Selects sampling locations
uniformly at random within the study area.
\item \strong{Stratified Random Sampling} (\code{\link[=ss_stratified]{ss_stratified()}}): Divides the study
area into compact strata and samples randomly within each stratum.
\item \strong{Spatial Coverage Sampling} (\code{\link[=ss_coverage]{ss_coverage()}}): Places samples at the
centroids of compact geographical strata for optimal spatial coverage.
}

The stratification is based on k-means clustering as described in
Walvoort et al. (2010). Two k-means algorithms are available:

\itemize{
\item \strong{Transfer algorithm}: Standard k-means that creates compact strata
of potentially unequal sizes.
\item \strong{Swop algorithm}: Creates compact strata of equal size, useful for
composite sampling.
}
