\section{When to Use Each Method}{


\itemize{
\item \strong{Spatial coverage sampling} (\code{\link[=ss_coverage]{ss_coverage()}}): Best for model-based
inference (kriging). Provides optimal spatial coverage for interpolation.
\item \strong{Stratified random sampling} (\code{\link[=ss_stratified]{ss_stratified()}}): Best for design-based
inference. Provides valid probability samples while ensuring coverage.
\item \strong{Simple random sampling} (\code{\link[=ss_random]{ss_random()}}): Use when no prior
stratification is desired. Valid for design-based inference.
\item \strong{Composite sampling} (\code{\link[=ss_composite]{ss_composite()}}): Use when samples will be
physically combined before analysis to reduce costs.
